onth()` returns the month in local time. If the environment's timezone isn't UTC, this would cause issues. But even in UTC, `getMonth()` on a `Z` date should be fine... unless the environment is set to a non-UTC timezone.\n\nRegardless, the code's intent (based on the comment \"UTC month\") is to use UTC methods, and `getMonth()` is not UTC-safe. The fix should be `getUTCMonth()`.\n\nNow let me apply all three fixes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":256,"cache_read_input_tokens":26013,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":256},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c69a063-4e3a-4645-b942-856872b3cfb8","uuid":"143d6b90-ba51-44ab-862b-5fe7f693f107"}
